contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary}} '''VE''', '''V-E''', '''V<sub>E</sub>''', '''Ve''' or '''ve''' may refer to: <!-- * [[Ve a Ve u Ve]] (?) --> * [[Vili and Vé]], gods in Norse mythology * [[Vé (shrine)]], a shrine in Germanic paganism and modern place name element * [[Ve (Cyrillic)]], a character from the Cyrillic alphabet * [[Ve (Arabic)]], a character of the Arabic alphabet * [[Vè]], a Vietnamese poetic form * "Ve", proposed [[gender-neutral pronoun]] * ''ve'', a [[Contraction (grammar)|contraction]] of the English auxiliary verb ''have'' ==Codes and acronyms== * [[Venezuela]], ISO, FIPS 10-4, and NATO (obsolete) country code VE, Internet TLD .ve * [[VE (nerve agent)]] (NATO designation), a chemical weapon agent * V-E Day, [[Victory in Europe Day]] * [[Venda language]], ISO 639 alpha-2, ve * [[Vertical exaggeration]], a vertical scaling used in technical diagrams * [[Volcanic Explosivity Index]], VE * [[Volumetric efficiency]] * [[vocational expert]] * VE, [[vinyl ester]] resin * [[Virtual environment]] (VE), a primary component of a Virtual Reality system * [[Virtual Earth]] * [[Valley Entertainment]], a U.S. record label and music distributor ==Science and medicine== * VE, [[Viliuisk Encephalomyelitis]] * V<sub>E</sub> denotes the [[Minute ventilation]] of the lungs (the volume of air expired by the lungs in one minute). ==Popular culture== *[[Viva Emptiness]] ==Transport== * [[Visalia Electric Railroad]], reporting marks VE * [[EUjet]], IATA airline designator * [[Avensa]], IATA airline designator * [[Volare Airlines]], IATA airline designator * [[Holden VE Commodore]], a model of the Holden Commodore, a car produced by GM Australia {{disambiguation}}
